Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.68,0:00:03.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Flowing water has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.49,0:00:05.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A blowing wind can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.31,0:00:07.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All cases can be freely deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.48,0:00:09.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mystery of Trick Ridge is coming to an end!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.22,0:00:11.34,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Heiji and I solve the mystery perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:12.89,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.89,0:00:14.95,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.95,0:00:17.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.16,0:01:48.52,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hattori and Kazuha are called out to the Takeda home
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:50.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}on Trick Ridge in Tottori Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.39,0:01:52.21,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The two get lost
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.21,0:01:54.91,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and meet up with a foreigner by the name of Robert Taylor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.86,0:02:00.18,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We were also called out to the Takeda home
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:01.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and accidentally met up with them on the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:07.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We were called to solve the mystery of the curse of the "Spider Mansion of Trick Ridge".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.39,0:02:11.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}On the night of our arrival,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.01,0:02:13.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, the eldest son of the Takeda family,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.50,0:02:15.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}committed suicide on the second floor of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.61,0:02:20.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In addition, Kazuha was attacked
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.33,0:02:24.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and found tangled in strings in the same warehouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.17,0:02:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.85,0:02:31.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.05,0:02:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Business card?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.74,0:02:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it out somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.39,0:02:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.54,0:02:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.54,0:02:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a stun gun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.19,0:02:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't see the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but she said she found a strange ball in front of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.13,0:02:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said it was a ball about this small.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:02:59.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}BB pellets!{UTB: BB shot!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.79,0:03:01.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.87,0:03:03.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I never thought of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.87,0:03:06.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If that's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.17,0:03:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it! Hattori, it's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.80,0:03:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.83,0:03:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange string with loops on the beam ends!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.42,0:03:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:20.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no mistake... That person is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.78,0:03:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery of the Spider Mansion of Tottori (Case Closed)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He figured out who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.26,0:03:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Did Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.23,0:03:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.30,0:03:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said for everyone to gather on the second floor of the warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.88,0:03:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also said to bring that big doll in the workshop too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.03,0:03:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also, it would help if there is some spare gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.03,0:04:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez. What's that kid from Osaka up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.58,0:04:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bringing the corpse down without permission...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.33,0:04:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he really say to wait here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.32,0:04:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.85,0:04:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.78,0:04:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.72,0:04:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let me start
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to tell you about the many incidents
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.58,0:04:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that have happened here at the Takedas' home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold up, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we found Brother, the door was locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only that one small window,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.13,0:04:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,barely large enough for a child to get through...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:54.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's a curse,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.17,0:04:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but if you say there's a killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,will you first explain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:05:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,how the killer escaped from this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.46,0:05:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there is a way like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.88,0:05:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who'd like to know how it was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.18,0:05:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.31,0:05:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer had no need to escape from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.53,0:05:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because when Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer wasn't in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.43,0:05:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.43,0:05:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strings used for the puppets!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer used puppet strings, ropes and thumbtacks
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.55,0:05:38.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to commit this locked room murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The setup is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.33,0:05:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, the rope is set up so that the loop closes when it is pulled,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.23,0:05:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and it is tied to the beam.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.71,0:05:50.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then with small loops made on both ends of the string,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the loop of the rope is pulled to four corners,{oi}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.87,0:05:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fixed to the small window with thumbtacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:06:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another long string is attached to the base of the loop of that rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.41,0:06:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is put over the beam in the center of the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.10,0:06:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and leads out the small window.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the setup is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.73,0:06:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Little boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that remains is to call Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,make him look out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.91,0:06:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pull the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.46,0:06:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The loop of the rope closes, and killing Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did Brother lock the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-And...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.35,0:06:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone would think it strange if he was told by the person he was waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.91,0:06:43.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to look out the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.80,0:06:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He locked the door
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because it was something important and he didn't want to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He looked out the window because he probably heard a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.02,0:06:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.32,0:07:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer fired BB pellets at the window with an air gun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.33,0:07:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would look out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to take revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.77,0:07:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who committed suicide here three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.80,0:07:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Revenge for Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.07,0:07:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.13,0:07:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably thought
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.68,0:07:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that Nobukazu, having found out that Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't his real daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.04,0:07:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,went hard on her, and forced her to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.24,0:07:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Not his real daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.55,0:07:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Ryūji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.51,0:07:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.36,0:07:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Yōko...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew I had to tell you sooner or later...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.15,0:07:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Misa...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.38,0:07:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That child...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is the daughter made between{OI OI}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,my brother's wife, Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.23,0:07:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're joking, aren't you? Dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.45,0:08:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was before I met you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.98,0:08:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was told at the hospital that Brother could not have children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.33,0:08:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she pleaded with me in tears...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"He wants a child", she said... "Please make his dream come true"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.61,0:08:20.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the first and last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.47,0:08:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother and I have the same blood type,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.63,0:08:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he wouldn't have found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.66,0:08:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the doctor at the hospital slipped his mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.89,0:08:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa ended up committing suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.30,0:08:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, feeling responsible, followed her...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.23,0:08:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's... It's all because I listened to her plead...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.80,0:08:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.43,0:08:52.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know I was Misa's father?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.56,0:08:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and I didn't tell anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.72,0:09:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the daughters of you and Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sae{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and Emi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, resemble each other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:06.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Misa -> Sae -> Emi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:06.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Misa
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:06.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sae
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:06.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Emi
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and form a circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.26,0:09:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recognized that and knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:13.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You secretly made the names of your daughters have a relation to one another. {oh geez}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.23,0:09:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It also seems like you were unusually upset
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s funerals...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mother named all the daughters...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.09,0:09:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.92,0:09:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I named the three to form a circle for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't take an old person for a fool!{maybe "I may be old, but I'm not stupid!"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.37,0:09:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Kinuyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came home from the hospital with the baby...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.71,0:09:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew right away from the way you two acted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't think you'd take revenge for the daughter's suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.89,0:09:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that Nobukazu was responsible for...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.64,0:10:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,making it look like the curse of the spider empress!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.84,0:10:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're disgusting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.84,0:10:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother, you're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.61,0:10:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't kill Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.64,0:10:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryūji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} isn't the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said it, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.93,0:10:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer fired an air gun at the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.45,0:10:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} looked out the window, the string was pulled
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.06,0:10:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.59,0:10:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if it was a locked room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.08,0:10:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if someone made movements in front of the warehouse like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.98,0:10:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he'd immediately be suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.06,0:10:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way this setup was done,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.71,0:10:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there would have to be superhuman strength used
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.41,0:10:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or the rate of failure would be very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.85,0:10:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make it successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you would need the strength
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.93,0:10:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to pull the thumbtacks on all four corners off at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.53,0:10:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who could have done that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.07,0:10:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,without being noticed by anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.97,0:10:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.78,0:11:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who could have done that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,without being noticed by anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.57,0:11:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used the car to visit the grave with the girls...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.77,0:11:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.83,0:11:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.26,0:11:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.52,0:11:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when you were going out to visit the grave,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.72,0:11:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you parked the car in front of the warehouse
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and waited for the girls to come running over to the waiting car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.46,0:11:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could have shot at the warehouse window from the driver's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.58,0:11:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And beforehand, you could have lead{o.o;} the string out the window
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.12,0:11:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you tied it to the car before dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.63,0:11:45.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you would have to do is drive the car off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.52,0:11:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd be able to pull with great strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.75,0:11:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string that was left on the car
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was retrieved in the mountains when you stopped to look at the scenery,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.70,0:11:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and was thrown away somewhere along with the air gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm definitely the one who moved the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it could've been someone else who tied the string to the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.71,0:12:14.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I haven't been here for three years. I just got here today!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.34,0:12:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely forgot where the house was, and got lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.65,0:12:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the time I got here to the time we went to visit the grave,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.17,0:12:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was with you almost the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.52,0:12:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have time to rig something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.69,0:12:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It hasn't been three years since you visited.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was only a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.90,0:12:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.99,0:12:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and rigged this setup on that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.84,0:12:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.80,0:12:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why only Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.34,0:12:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He avoided this room that was rigged with the setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.88,0:12:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He called the high school detective from Osaka with a strange request letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.01,0:12:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He made the meeting on the road look accidental
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like he hadn't been here for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would suspect someone who was lost
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.56,0:13:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and picked by an Osaka detective on the road
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.92,0:13:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to have something like this set up beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.99,0:13:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But why kill Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.97,0:13:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.53,0:13:23.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I know for sure that Robert{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} found out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.47,0:13:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,about Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s suicide and the narcotics at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.71,0:13:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Narcotics?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} worked with Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.19,0:13:34.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,stuffing the dolls with narcotics
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.37,0:13:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and selling them at a high price.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother dealing narcotics?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.37,0:13:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't believe me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.53,0:13:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,check the dolls in the workshop later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dolls are filled with narcotics.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.11,0:13:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after killing Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.43,0:14:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert stole one of the narcotic-stuffed dolls that he was planning to take with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next day, he made the plans to call Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out to this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you're interested in narcotics, I've got some good drugs. Wanna make a deal?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably what he said on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} suspected someone in the family of killing Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and stealing the drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he jumped at the phone call!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.94,0:14:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was called out to this room, where the trap was set
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.60,0:14:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.80,0:14:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.23,0:14:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't have proof and you're making false accusations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.57,0:14:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you're forgetting something important!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.49,0:14:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Explain the mystery of why Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was tangled in the strings!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.04,0:14:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.17,0:14:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.06,0:15:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, old man! I'm ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.04,0:15:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.66,0:15:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I completely forgot about it until you mentioned it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.39,0:15:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that thing about Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} being tangled in the strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That setup has been taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hasn't it, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look. It was dark and you probably didn't see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but strings are attached to the rope that's tied to the beam!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.39,0:15:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Proof rather than discussion... Let's actually try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Yūzō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.36,0:15:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stick the head of the doll you have out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.50,0:15:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like how Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} looked out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.44,0:15:54.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert confirmed the situation and then moved the car away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.72,0:16:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string tied to the car is pulled,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.23,0:16:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the thumbtacks come loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.72,0:16:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the rope choked Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it pulled in the opposite direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.01,0:16:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the back of Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s head bangs against the beam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string is pulled more, and it snaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.54,0:16:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body dives into a sea of strings
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tangles from the ceiling, as if tangled in a spider's threads!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.45,0:16:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question, Robert{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.57,0:16:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know that Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was tangled in strings?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.44,0:16:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones among you who knew about it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.76,0:16:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were Ryūji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Yūzō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Chie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the four who came to the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.83,0:16:53.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, those four were told not to tell anyone about the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.49,0:16:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And one more person...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.39,0:16:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.39,0:17:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the one who rigged the setup to kill Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.01,0:17:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sounds funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.44,0:17:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You kept everyone from talking and waited for me to make the slip!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.12,0:17:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The number of fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.12,0:17:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fish we had for dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.29,0:17:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The unexpected guests were supposed to be the three of us—me, Kazuha and you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.32,0:17:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she was short only two fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.30,0:17:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means that you were an expected guest that someone had already invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.30,0:17:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, I thought that you and Yōko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who bought the fish, were suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.71,0:17:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But hearing that Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} handled all the money,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.12,0:17:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the only suspicious one left was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sensed something was going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing had happened yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.76,0:18:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I let Kazuha go to visit the grave with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.32,0:18:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Nobukazu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered, and I panicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.58,0:18:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were the killer, you might have run off with Kazuha to find Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.66,0:18:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You dangled Kazuha in the strings on the first floor of the warehouse
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.47,0:18:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but didn't kill her, to make it look like a curse,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and to create an illusion to make us think that there is a way to escape from this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, there's also the reason that Kazuha found the BB shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But why? Why even Negishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Several days ago, when I came by here, he said this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.82,0:18:47.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If it's Misa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-chan{\r\be10} you're looking for, she committed suicide after you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.65,0:18:50.52,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nobukazu was picking on her anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:55.55,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well, it can't be helped. She wasn't his real daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.55,0:18:59.91,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A girl like that... Nobody'd marry her anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.91,0:19:03.72,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There'd be nothing good even if she were living.{?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.79,0:19:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With eyes that were high on drugs...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He laughed and told me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.93,0:19:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I desperately learned to read and write Japanese
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because she wasn't good at English...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.84,0:19:19.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was finally able to come and meet her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.09,0:19:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I looked forward to seeing her smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.88,0:19:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you think you overdid it, putting Kazuha in that situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't care who got hurt, or who suspected me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even everyone in this household, who let her die!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.94,0:19:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I didn't plan on telling you, but I'll tell you anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in an unstable state of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when she was conversing with you in roman-Japanese,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.62,0:19:55.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Stop, Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.60,0:19:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real reason she committed suicide was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,maybe... just maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.18,0:20:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shine"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.09,0:20:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-H-I-N-E is "shine".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means to be bright.{oh geez}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.95,0:20:20.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe for Robert, Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a bright light.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.09,0:20:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Light?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.46,0:20:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Robert said
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.64,0:20:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he wanted a bride that was like a light...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.27,0:20:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got to apologize to Robert!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.32,0:20:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apologize?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.98,0:20:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was the same as the letters from Uncle Negishi{or Negishi-ojisan? how wapa we want to get?}'s name...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.96,0:20:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we thought Robert wrote a terrible thing and gave it to Misa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.57,0:20:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought he wrote "die" (shine)...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.50,0:21:04.10,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Morning came, and Robert was taken away by the Tottori Prefectural Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:06.91,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In the police car,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.91,0:21:11.66,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Robert repeated the same words over and over again...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.08,0:21:15.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Why wasn't I Japanese?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.31,0:21:19.95,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Why wasn't she American?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.33,0:21:24.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Like a broken puppet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.86,0:21:27.95,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}he repeated over and over again...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.99,0:22:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.73,0:23:02.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did Robert go off with the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.86,0:23:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the killer is the spider empress...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.35,0:23:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.82,0:23:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we went to take a bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.11,0:23:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we saw that long spider's thread coming out of the warehouse window!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.61,0:23:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.04,0:23:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.81,0:23:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the doing of the spider empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.00,0:23:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Robert just went back to his country. There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.62,0:23:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.57,0:23:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.01,0:23:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Granny, tell us a story again!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.57,0:23:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about The White Rabbit of Inaba?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.50,0:23:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've heard that one before!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.08,0:23:45.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's Grandma, after all...{this line needs a rewrite}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.98,0:23:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.25,0:23:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.91,0:23:59.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Drowning?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.18,0:24:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, due to some sort of accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.89,0:24:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she wasn't able to escape from the shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.46,0:24:10.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No. This isn't an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.18,0:24:11.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's premeditated murder!
